1
00:00:08,578 --> 00:00:13,141
As surgeons, we rely on cycles.

2
00:00:13,260 --> 00:00:14,764
Heartbeats.

3
00:00:14,774 --> 00:00:16,603
Cell regeneration.

4
00:00:16,803 --> 00:00:19,288
Circadian rhythms.

5
00:00:19,934 --> 00:00:23,037
We know something's wrong
when the cycle is broken.

6
00:00:23,278 --> 00:00:24,991
Our duty is to fix it.

7
00:00:25,710 --> 00:00:27,639
To force the cogs
back in line.

8
00:00:29,804 --> 00:00:31,683
Sorry, sir!
Morning, sir!

9
00:00:33,128 --> 00:00:36,974
But that break can also be
useful, like a warning shot.

10
00:00:46,769 --> 00:00:48,938
Beth, please. I know.

11
00:00:49,034 --> 00:00:51,194
Y-Yeah, my leave
was canceled. I...

12
00:00:51,296 --> 00:00:53,912
Don't cry. I will make this
up to you, I promise.

13
00:00:53,975 --> 00:00:55,456
She's got that vice grip
so tight,

14
00:00:55,514 --> 00:00:56,912
his testicles
are about to pop off.

15
00:00:56,970 --> 00:00:58,058
How you holding up?

16
00:00:58,116 --> 00:01:00,022
Well, considering
that today decides

17
00:01:00,080 --> 00:01:01,506
my entire military future?
Medium.

18
00:01:01,574 --> 00:01:02,873
You're a shoo-in.

19
00:01:03,061 --> 00:01:05,721
I think I'd rather focus on
my brother's pathetic love life.

20
00:01:05,917 --> 00:01:09,026
- Hey, that was an endearing conversation.
- How's everything at home?

21
00:01:09,084 --> 00:01:10,702
All right. Let's focus on
getting this stuff loaded.

22
00:01:10,759 --> 00:01:12,318
We need to be in Fallujah
at 0700.

23
00:01:12,376 --> 00:01:13,985
I'd like to be
less uptight by 0700.

24
00:01:14,110 --> 00:01:17,337
Okay. Save it. The colonel's
coming. Where the hell is Riggs?

25
00:01:17,618 --> 00:01:20,501
He was on call last night.
I'll get him.

26
00:01:24,595 --> 00:01:27,322
Owen. Owen.

27
00:01:28,226 --> 00:01:29,673
Owen!

28
00:01:29,976 --> 00:01:31,000
Are you okay?

29
00:01:31,243 --> 00:01:33,563
Uh, yeah.
Yeah, I'm okay.

30
00:01:37,472 --> 00:01:39,955
It's...
It's not really goodbye.

31
00:01:40,110 --> 00:01:43,298
I mean, Los Angeles
is a two-hour flight,

32
00:01:43,368 --> 00:01:45,618
so you can see her
whenever you want.

33
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,118
Yeah.

34
00:01:50,242 --> 00:01:52,142
How 'bout I make us
dinner tonight?

35
00:01:54,399 --> 00:01:56,278
Well, that
would be... nice.

36
00:02:01,188 --> 00:02:03,397
Hey! I'm getting
on the road now.

37
00:02:03,455 --> 00:02:04,845
How long till you're here?

38
00:02:04,993 --> 00:02:06,524
Uh, it's...
It's a long drive.

39
00:02:06,610 --> 00:02:09,485
Well, if you drive faster,
will you get here sooner?

40
00:02:09,634 --> 00:02:11,321
Just help Nathan
get everything ready,

41
00:02:11,379 --> 00:02:12,669
and you won't even
notice the time.

42
00:02:12,726 --> 00:02:14,290
Aah! Son of a...

43
00:02:14,643 --> 00:02:15,696
Doubt it.

44
00:02:15,754 --> 00:02:16,810
Kisses, my sweet boy.

45
00:02:16,868 --> 00:02:18,470
Hey, will you give Nate
the phone?

46
00:02:20,751 --> 00:02:22,267
Oh. Thanks, buddy.

47
00:02:22,548 --> 00:02:24,470
- Hey, baby, how's it going?
- How's he doing?

48
00:02:24,528 --> 00:02:26,457
God. This has got to
be totally overwhelming for him.

49
00:02:26,514 --> 00:02:28,445
- No, no, no.
- We're... We're having a blast.

50
00:02:28,503 --> 00:02:29,820
And you got
his fan, right?

51
00:02:29,878 --> 00:02:31,274
I mean, he cannot sleep
without his fan.

52
00:02:31,331 --> 00:02:34,463
Uh, fan. Fan. Uh...

53
00:02:35,307 --> 00:02:37,338
Well, I'm not sure if...

54
00:02:37,682 --> 00:02:39,049
Oh, yeah.

55
00:02:39,182 --> 00:02:40,932
- We got it.
- Okay.

56
00:02:40,990 --> 00:02:43,893
Now we just got to figure out
how to put it together.

57
00:02:47,995 --> 00:02:49,331
What was that?

58
00:02:50,307 --> 00:02:51,674
Uh, uh, I don't know.

59
00:02:51,732 --> 00:02:52,942
I didn't...
I didn't hear anything.

60
00:02:52,999 --> 00:02:54,182
Did you hear anything,
Farouk?

61
00:02:54,332 --> 00:02:55,659
The door falling!

62
00:02:55,985 --> 00:02:58,068
Shh. No. No, he didn't...
He didn't hear anything, either.

63
00:02:58,125 --> 00:03:00,099
Mm-hmm.

64
00:03:04,276 --> 00:03:06,445
- Incoming!
- Aah!

65
00:03:10,174 --> 00:03:11,823
You're gonna kill me
one of these days.

66
00:03:11,881 --> 00:03:13,515
Oh, you love it.

67
00:03:17,151 --> 00:03:18,595
So, are we done fighting?

68
00:03:18,662 --> 00:03:20,260
You tell me.

69
00:03:22,661 --> 00:03:24,248
Come here.

70
00:03:28,350 --> 00:03:30,245
- We're going to Fallujah.
- Hmm?

71
00:03:30,303 --> 00:03:31,175
We're going to Fallujah!

72
00:03:31,233 --> 00:03:31,949
Mnh-mnh.
Uh-huh.

73
00:03:32,016 --> 00:03:34,095
I prefer the relative
safety of Baghdad...

74
00:03:34,162 --> 00:03:36,119
and this bed.

75
00:03:36,186 --> 00:03:39,128
No. No. I can't be late.
I can't be late. Not today.

76
00:03:39,222 --> 00:03:40,935
Oh, right. Your thing.

77
00:03:41,002 --> 00:03:44,409
The, um, the strack?
The strap? Strack?

78
00:03:44,476 --> 00:03:46,779
Strat!
As in stratification.

79
00:03:46,846 --> 00:03:48,831
As in if I don't get
ranked number one,

80
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:51,737
I can kiss flight surgeon
goodbye, so...

81
00:04:03,107 --> 00:04:05,276
You weren't supposed to
find that.

82
00:04:07,575 --> 00:04:11,067
I know it's not exactly a ring,
but, as I recall,

83
00:04:11,134 --> 00:04:14,380
you... you lost your class ring
in the surgical sink, so...

84
00:04:14,472 --> 00:04:15,696
Not a ring?

85
00:04:17,403 --> 00:04:20,278
Don't you dare do the thing,
unless you are doing the thing.

86
00:04:21,138 --> 00:04:23,304
Oh, my God. You are doing it.

87
00:04:23,362 --> 00:04:25,576
Megan Eloise Hunt,
will you... Yes!!

88
00:04:27,256 --> 00:04:29,006
Yes. Yes.

89
00:04:31,964 --> 00:04:33,530
Let's go!

90
00:04:35,674 --> 00:04:37,631
Come on!
What kept you?!

91
00:04:37,701 --> 00:04:38,817
I said yes!

92
00:04:38,884 --> 00:04:40,147
- What?!
- Aah!

93
00:04:40,214 --> 00:04:42,053
And I asked her
to marry me!

94
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:44,890
- Aah! Congratulations!
- About time!

95
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:46,757
Mwah!

96
00:04:46,815 --> 00:04:48,210
Oh, wait.
Look. Look, look.

97
00:04:48,268 --> 00:04:51,593
Wow! An engagement
necklace?

98
00:04:52,076 --> 00:04:53,819
Wow.
That's interesting.

99
00:04:53,877 --> 00:04:57,456
Yeah, well, she loses everything
that's not tied to her, so...

100
00:05:16,844 --> 00:05:19,357
Malibu... it's too far
away, and it's too snooty.

101
00:05:19,415 --> 00:05:21,804
You're gonna hate it.
And Seattle has beaches.

102
00:05:21,862 --> 00:05:23,571
Freezing-cold beaches.
Not the same.

103
00:05:24,284 --> 00:05:25,710
Nathan found a job yet?

104
00:05:25,768 --> 00:05:26,772
He will.

105
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:29,382
And if he doesn't, I'm sure
I could find some pole work.

106
00:05:29,448 --> 00:05:31,461
- Megan.
- I will come home for Christmas.

107
00:05:31,519 --> 00:05:32,780
And you'll come
visit me a lot,

108
00:05:32,838 --> 00:05:35,398
which will be so good
for you because, you know...

109
00:05:35,719 --> 00:05:37,366
the sun.

110
00:05:41,251 --> 00:05:42,830
I'll miss you, Eeyore.

111
00:05:44,275 --> 00:05:45,775
Come here.

112
00:05:48,624 --> 00:05:50,124
- Okay.
- Okay.

113
00:05:52,262 --> 00:05:53,801
Bye.

114
00:05:56,485 --> 00:05:57,998
Colonel's convoy inbound.

115
00:05:58,065 --> 00:06:00,219
All right, gents.
Chins up, backs straight.

116
00:06:00,363 --> 00:06:02,375
Stand with dignity,
not sloppiness.

117
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:03,875
I'm talking to you,
Sergeant!

118
00:06:03,933 --> 00:06:05,539
Yes, sir,
Major Diamond, sir!

119
00:06:06,522 --> 00:06:07,961
I just don't
want to be ranked last.

120
00:06:08,019 --> 00:06:09,984
Tubs failed his PT test.
He's last.

121
00:06:10,042 --> 00:06:11,638
We're all gunning
for second place anyway.

122
00:06:11,695 --> 00:06:13,098
You know Hunt's stratted
number one.

123
00:06:13,156 --> 00:06:14,703
The best will be first,
so, yeah, you're right.

124
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:15,920
Wish my brother
was the C.O.

125
00:06:15,983 --> 00:06:18,077
Your mom could be C.O.
and you'd still be last.

126
00:06:20,276 --> 00:06:21,616
At-ten-hut!

127
00:06:33,084 --> 00:06:34,624
At ease.

128
00:06:36,011 --> 00:06:37,534
Excellent work,
Major Hunt.

129
00:06:37,799 --> 00:06:39,401
Before I get started
on this tour,

130
00:06:39,459 --> 00:06:41,424
let's get to what
you all really want to know...

131
00:06:41,790 --> 00:06:43,013
My strat rankings.

132
00:06:43,071 --> 00:06:44,589
It was a difficult decision,

133
00:06:44,675 --> 00:06:47,596
but join me in congratulating
Lieutenant John Matthews.

134
00:06:51,045 --> 00:06:54,221
♪♪

135
00:06:54,279 --> 00:06:56,948
♪♪

136
00:06:57,006 --> 00:06:59,174
Talon 1 to Sparrow.
We have an emergency inbound. Copy?

137
00:06:59,232 --> 00:07:00,253
Talon 1, copy that.

138
00:07:00,311 --> 00:07:02,542
Marine FOB Ace Hole
reports two active shooters.

139
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:04,782
We have four KIA and
20 wounded headed your way.

140
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:06,065
Copy that.
We'll be ready. Out.

141
00:07:06,123 --> 00:07:09,596
All surgeons on deck!
Frontload supplies! Fall out!

142
00:07:10,321 --> 00:07:14,112
♪♪

143
00:07:14,456 --> 00:07:18,192
We have

144
00:07:21,625 --> 00:07:23,417
- What are you doing?
- I'm coming with you.

145
00:07:23,792 --> 00:07:25,028
What?

146
00:07:25,086 --> 00:07:26,401
Road trip.

147
00:07:26,799 --> 00:07:28,073
Are you serious?

148
00:07:28,131 --> 00:07:30,096
You said you wanted
to beat traffic.

149
00:07:31,219 --> 00:07:33,218
What are you waiting for?
Drive!

150
00:07:41,136 --> 00:07:43,467
Are you sure about this?
I can just drop you at the corner.

151
00:07:43,524 --> 00:07:45,813
Shut up. I love road trips.
Since when?

152
00:07:45,871 --> 00:07:47,898
Since we were kids.
Roadtripping with Mom and Dad.

153
00:07:47,956 --> 00:07:49,623
You used to hate
those trips!

154
00:07:49,681 --> 00:07:51,234
We... We would fight
so much

155
00:07:51,292 --> 00:07:53,351
that Mom and Dad would threaten
to leave us at a gas station.

156
00:07:53,367 --> 00:07:55,144
Well, fortunately,
we're grown-ups now.

157
00:07:55,202 --> 00:07:56,156
How do you work
this radio?

158
00:07:56,214 --> 00:07:58,525
I'm just saying...
I don't need a babysitter.

159
00:07:58,583 --> 00:08:00,514
I am not a babysitter,
I'm a copilot.

160
00:08:00,572 --> 00:08:02,393
Here to
ensure you don't fall asleep,

161
00:08:02,451 --> 00:08:03,926
swerve off a cliff
to a fiery death.

162
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:06,221
We're driving straight through.
No detours.

163
00:08:06,279 --> 00:08:09,111
Whatever you say.
I'm just along for the ride.

164
00:08:09,355 --> 00:08:12,400
♪♪

165
00:08:13,134 --> 00:08:14,182
Superficial laceration.

166
00:08:14,231 --> 00:08:16,080
See that nurse over there
for steri-strips.

167
00:08:16,143 --> 00:08:18,098
Matthews is top strat?
What the hell happened?

168
00:08:18,184 --> 00:08:20,068
- The Colonel has the final say.
- Go. How hard did you push?

169
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:21,482
Did you tell him that
I was CGO of the year?

170
00:08:21,539 --> 00:08:24,168
Of course! You know how
political these things are.

171
00:08:24,231 --> 00:08:26,192
I'm never gonna get
flight-surgeon training now.

172
00:08:26,266 --> 00:08:28,403
- Okay, let's go.
- Come on, guys! Come on through!

173
00:08:28,461 --> 00:08:32,368
PFC Tyler Budreaux.
Pulse 90s, BP 100s over 50s.

174
00:08:32,942 --> 00:08:35,699
I'd salute you, sir,
but I can't feel my arm.

175
00:08:35,757 --> 00:08:37,314
What happened out there?
Two of the Iraqi allies

176
00:08:37,371 --> 00:08:38,434
went rogue. Opened fire.

177
00:08:38,492 --> 00:08:39,856
Tyler pushed people
out of the way.

178
00:08:39,914 --> 00:08:41,318
You're looking at a
freakin' American hero, sir.

179
00:08:41,375 --> 00:08:42,543
I really do need
my arm, sir.

180
00:08:42,655 --> 00:08:43,965
We're gonna do
everything we can.

181
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:46,383
Hang two grams of cefazolin
and get him prepped for the O.R.

182
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:50,465
Stop! Stop! She doesn't...
Wait! Stop!

183
00:08:50,523 --> 00:08:52,504
Don't touch her! She doesn't
want to be touched by men!

184
00:08:52,561 --> 00:08:54,371
Hey, listen.
I got this. You go.

185
00:08:55,902 --> 00:08:57,957
Hey, hey, I got it. Here.
Get out of the way.

186
00:08:58,023 --> 00:09:00,206
"GSW upper right chest.
Diminished breathing sounds."

187
00:09:00,264 --> 00:09:01,407
She needs a chest tube.

188
00:09:06,705 --> 00:09:07,994
All right.
Let me take a look.

189
00:09:08,052 --> 00:09:11,166
- Where do you want him?
- Shrapnel wound. Pre-op.

190
00:09:11,411 --> 00:09:12,743
What do we have?

191
00:09:12,801 --> 00:09:15,705
Nadir al-Jabouri.
Multiple GSWs to the torso.

192
00:09:15,763 --> 00:09:17,376
Perp believed to be
the second shooter.

193
00:09:17,434 --> 00:09:19,307
- And he's still alive?
- Unfortunately.

194
00:09:19,365 --> 00:09:20,541
You treat that woman well.

195
00:09:20,599 --> 00:09:21,987
'Cause she saved
everyone's ass!

196
00:09:22,045 --> 00:09:24,041
Tried to wrestle
his gun from him.

197
00:09:24,353 --> 00:09:27,276
He needs an ex lap.
O.R. ASAP. Let's go.

198
00:09:27,396 --> 00:09:29,729
- Nathan, scrub in with me?
- You got it.

199
00:09:29,787 --> 00:09:31,430
Let's go! Let's go!

200
00:09:32,970 --> 00:09:34,698
We'll make your bed
a racecar,

201
00:09:34,756 --> 00:09:36,666
so you can go really fast
in your dreams.

202
00:09:36,737 --> 00:09:37,916
A race car?

203
00:09:37,974 --> 00:09:40,510
Yeah, you know,
like NASCAR or Formula 1?

204
00:09:40,568 --> 00:09:42,807
It's a car that goes
really, really fast.

205
00:09:42,865 --> 00:09:45,065
- My bed?
- Trust me, it's cool.

206
00:09:45,131 --> 00:09:47,080
Then where will
Mama sleep?

207
00:09:47,138 --> 00:09:50,213
Well, in her room. Our room.
It's just across the hall.

208
00:09:50,310 --> 00:09:53,151
But back home, we used to
sleep in the same room.

209
00:09:53,632 --> 00:09:54,948
It's safer that way.

210
00:09:55,006 --> 00:09:56,588
This is home now,
buddy.

211
00:09:59,136 --> 00:10:01,073
Hey, I know
it's an adjustment, okay?

212
00:10:01,131 --> 00:10:02,933
But once you start school,
you're gonna feel settled.

213
00:10:02,990 --> 00:10:04,393
Mama has always been
my teacher

214
00:10:04,451 --> 00:10:05,713
Well, now she
won't need to be.

215
00:10:05,771 --> 00:10:08,202
You're gonna get to go to school
with a bunch of kids your own age.

216
00:10:08,259 --> 00:10:09,776
You're gonna make
lots of friends.

217
00:10:09,834 --> 00:10:11,987
Maybe join the band, you know?
You can play sports.

218
00:10:12,045 --> 00:10:14,143
Soccer, baseball.
You're gonna love it.

219
00:10:15,330 --> 00:10:17,174
I'm sorry! So sorry!

220
00:10:17,232 --> 00:10:19,484
It's okay. It's okay.
But you got bare feet. Hang on.

221
00:10:19,542 --> 00:10:21,718
There you go.
You're all right.

222
00:10:25,978 --> 00:10:28,804
See? Not a problem.

223
00:10:38,430 --> 00:10:39,859
That really is

224
00:10:39,917 --> 00:10:42,416
a beautiful necklace
that you got for Megan.

225
00:10:42,474 --> 00:10:45,171
Where'd you find
emeralds in Baghdad?

226
00:10:45,229 --> 00:10:46,702
You want one
for yourself?

227
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:47,883
You seem awfully stuck
on it.

228
00:10:47,941 --> 00:10:49,650
It just reminds me
so much of the necklace

229
00:10:49,708 --> 00:10:52,226
that Sergeant Philips got
from her boyfriend back home.

230
00:10:52,281 --> 00:10:53,424
You know...

231
00:10:53,968 --> 00:10:55,343
Felicia Philips?

232
00:10:55,695 --> 00:10:59,634
Well, but hers in engraved
with her initials on the back.

233
00:10:59,780 --> 00:11:01,045
It's engraved?

234
00:11:01,445 --> 00:11:03,117
Yep.

235
00:11:03,870 --> 00:11:05,160
Ten blade.

236
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:09,212
♪ Can't you hear
that music pumpin' hard ♪

237
00:11:09,270 --> 00:11:10,532
♪ Like I wish you would? ♪

238
00:11:10,590 --> 00:11:11,747
♪ Now push it ♪

239
00:11:11,805 --> 00:11:13,738
♪ Ner, ner-ner,
ner-ner, enh ♪

240
00:11:13,809 --> 00:11:15,501
♪ Push it good! ♪

241
00:11:16,878 --> 00:11:19,197
♪ P-Push it real good! ♪

242
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:21,929
Hey, open these for me,
will ya?

243
00:11:21,987 --> 00:11:23,788
Ew! No.

244
00:11:23,846 --> 00:11:25,617
What? There's no
food in that food.

245
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:27,795
- I'm starving!
- You can eat next time we stop for gas.

246
00:11:27,852 --> 00:11:30,455
♪♪

247
00:11:31,661 --> 00:11:33,004
♪ Get up on this ♪

248
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:38,035
Please return
to the highlighted route.

249
00:11:38,093 --> 00:11:40,066
