do this to her?

500
00:23:48,524 --> 00:23:50,872
I don't know.
We were fighting...

501
00:23:50,997 --> 00:23:52,606
You were fighting,
so you proposed to her

502
00:23:52,664 --> 00:23:54,708
with your side piece's
stolen property?

503
00:23:54,807 --> 00:23:56,872
No. Look.
Felicia's not...

504
00:23:56,930 --> 00:23:58,888
It was a one-time thing.

505
00:23:59,883 --> 00:24:01,598
What am I gonna do,
Teddy?

506
00:24:03,575 --> 00:24:05,825
Did you mean it?
The proposal?

507
00:24:05,883 --> 00:24:08,567
Of course.
Look. Megan...

508
00:24:08,740 --> 00:24:10,472
Okay, we fight.
But she's the one.

509
00:24:10,530 --> 00:24:12,106
Okay? I was gonna tell her
about Felicia.

510
00:24:12,138 --> 00:24:13,849
I was gonna come clean.
And then she found the necklace.

511
00:24:13,906 --> 00:24:15,673
And I... I panicked.

512
00:24:15,731 --> 00:24:17,201
- Well, she's gonna find out.
- I know.

513
00:24:17,258 --> 00:24:18,654
And if it comes from
anyone but you...

514
00:24:18,711 --> 00:24:19,821
I know.

515
00:24:19,947 --> 00:24:21,245
Well, so...

516
00:24:21,448 --> 00:24:22,888
you have your answer.

517
00:24:24,022 --> 00:24:25,971
Well, you think
there's a chance?

518
00:24:28,245 --> 00:24:30,323
Well, she's got a temper,

519
00:24:30,932 --> 00:24:32,596
and she has every right
to be angry.

520
00:24:32,654 --> 00:24:34,721
And when Owen finds out, he is
gonna snap your neck.

521
00:24:34,779 --> 00:24:36,502
- Yeah.
- But...

522
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:39,463
people mess up.

523
00:24:39,926 --> 00:24:41,643
And people forgive.

524
00:24:43,862 --> 00:24:46,666
It's what most pop songs and
most modern literature is about,

525
00:24:46,724 --> 00:24:48,448
so, yes, Nathan...

526
00:24:48,541 --> 00:24:51,979
tell her the truth,
and there's a chance.

527
00:25:08,611 --> 00:25:11,284
It was wrong of me to get in
the way of your career.

528
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:14,690
It was none of my business.
I was out of line.

529
00:25:15,854 --> 00:25:18,263
It was just... just wrong.
And I'm sorry.

530
00:25:18,762 --> 00:25:20,182
Thank you.

531
00:25:23,355 --> 00:25:25,718
But it doesn't change the fact that
Seattle schools are excellent.

532
00:25:25,775 --> 00:25:26,798
Oh, my God!
Give it a rest!

533
00:25:26,855 --> 00:25:29,764
Nathan already has a job there,
plus it's safer, familiar.

534
00:25:29,822 --> 00:25:30,920
Closer to family.

535
00:25:30,986 --> 00:25:32,795
Whoa. What are you doing?

536
00:25:33,939 --> 00:25:36,208
Get out!
Get out of my car, Owen!

537
00:25:36,337 --> 00:25:37,734
Stop being ridiculous.

538
00:25:37,801 --> 00:25:39,707
- No! Get out!
- Stop it!

539
00:25:40,017 --> 00:25:41,691
What do you mean,
Megan's not coming?

540
00:25:41,749 --> 00:25:43,772
Well, she thinks you tanked
her strat. She's mad.

541
00:25:43,830 --> 00:25:45,473
Well, I hope you told her
she was crazy.

542
00:25:45,573 --> 00:25:48,465
- Is she?
- Oh, great. Not you, too?

543
00:25:48,605 --> 00:25:50,375
I'm just asking.
I'm not accusing.

544
00:25:50,433 --> 00:25:51,652
You know what?
She got engaged.

545
00:25:51,710 --> 00:25:53,926
You'd think she'd want to
live a safe, happy life.

546
00:25:53,984 --> 00:25:56,097
Plan a wedding, maybe.
Is that such a crazy thought?

547
00:25:56,155 --> 00:25:58,878
God! She wanted
that strat, Owen.

548
00:25:58,921 --> 00:26:01,121
It's all she thinks about.
And she was so close.

549
00:26:01,179 --> 00:26:02,714
Do you know how hard it is
to stand by

550
00:26:02,772 --> 00:26:04,855
and watch someone else
live the life that you want?

551
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:07,723
The life that you're willing
to give up everything for?

552
00:26:07,842 --> 00:26:09,249
You're an idiot!

553
00:26:09,317 --> 00:26:11,527
Major,
we need to head out!

554
00:26:13,316 --> 00:26:15,245
Well, make sure Megan
rides back with you guys.

555
00:26:15,303 --> 00:26:17,406
I can only tolerate
so many tantrums.

556
00:26:35,403 --> 00:26:36,493
Get out!

557
00:26:38,396 --> 00:26:39,645
Get out! I mean it!

558
00:26:39,703 --> 00:26:41,075
- Stop this.
- No.

559
00:26:41,133 --> 00:26:42,716
If you can't support me,
then you can hitchhike.

560
00:26:42,773 --> 00:26:44,193
- Because I am done. Get out!
- Stop it!

561
00:26:44,250 --> 00:26:45,669
I'm not leaving you again!

562
00:26:49,117 --> 00:26:51,145
You have to stop
doing this.

563
00:26:51,340 --> 00:26:53,778
You... You can't keep making
decisions for me, Owen.

564
00:26:53,836 --> 00:26:55,138
'Cause you are making
a bad decision.

565
00:26:55,195 --> 00:26:56,682
You are the only one
who thinks that.

566
00:26:56,740 --> 00:26:58,318
Nathan's the reason
we lost you in the first place.

567
00:26:58,375 --> 00:26:59,863
You don't know what
you're talking about!

568
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,513
He cheated on you and now you're
starting a family with him?

569
00:27:01,570 --> 00:27:03,372
And you cheated
on your first wife.

570
00:27:03,580 --> 00:27:05,426
Mom told me all about it.

571
00:27:05,484 --> 00:27:07,926
And don't even get me started
on you and Teddy.

572
00:27:08,067 --> 00:27:10,340
So spare me
the "holier than thou" crap.

573
00:27:10,398 --> 00:27:12,527
You cheated, Nathan cheated.
It happens.

574
00:27:12,585 --> 00:27:15,731
Life happens.
People are imperfect.

575
00:27:15,789 --> 00:27:19,842
We fail and we fall, and some of
us get kidnapped for a decade,

576
00:27:19,900 --> 00:27:21,880
and when we get a second chance
at life and happiness,

577
00:27:21,937 --> 00:27:24,223
we seize it,
regardless of who cheated!

578
00:27:24,281 --> 00:27:25,934
Because now we know
what matters.

579
00:27:25,992 --> 00:27:28,028
Because now we know
what's precious.

580
00:27:28,110 --> 00:27:29,253
Because now we know that

581
00:27:29,422 --> 00:27:31,036
any tiny little moment
of happiness

582
00:27:31,094 --> 00:27:32,762
that we can grab onto
in this lifetime

583
00:27:32,820 --> 00:27:34,807
is a moment worth having,

584
00:27:34,865 --> 00:27:36,872
regardless of what
anyone else thinks.

585
00:27:37,014 --> 00:27:39,340
And just for the record,
you judgmental jackass,

586
00:27:39,446 --> 00:27:41,020
I cheated on Nathan first!

587
00:28:09,732 --> 00:28:10,932
Hey.

588
00:28:20,499 --> 00:28:23,369
- What's wrong?
- I'm sorry. I, um...

589
00:28:24,906 --> 00:28:26,562
I need
that necklace back.

590
00:28:29,857 --> 00:28:31,703
Damn it. Damn it!

591
00:28:31,761 --> 00:28:33,560
- Just hear me out.
- Okay, what did he say?

592
00:28:33,618 --> 00:28:35,531
No. You know what?
It doesn't matter.

593
00:28:35,589 --> 00:28:37,086
It was a drunken mistake.

594
00:28:37,144 --> 00:28:38,969
You and I were fighting,
and I was gonna tell you...

595
00:28:39,026 --> 00:28:41,109
Whoa, whoa. Hang on a second.
What are you saying?

596
00:28:41,571 --> 00:28:43,085
W-What do you think
I'm saying?

597
00:28:43,143 --> 00:28:44,438
Well, it sounds like
you slept with someone.

598
00:28:44,495 --> 00:28:46,071
Isn't that why you want
the necklace back?

599
00:28:46,128 --> 00:28:47,554
No! It...

600
00:28:48,835 --> 00:28:51,351
Then what?

601
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:55,430
W-Wasn't mine to give.

602
00:29:02,016 --> 00:29:05,984
You proposed to me with
some other chick's necklace?!

603
00:29:07,892 --> 00:29:09,749
God, Nathan!
What is wrong with you?!

604
00:29:09,807 --> 00:29:12,492
Okay, you're not the only one that
gets to be mad right now, okay?

605
00:29:12,611 --> 00:29:14,171
You cheated, too.
You just said.

606
00:29:14,229 --> 00:29:15,523
I know what I said.

607
00:29:17,037 --> 00:29:18,718
I have been showing
that thing off all day.

608
00:29:18,776 --> 00:29:21,039
This is so humiliating.

609
00:29:21,275 --> 00:29:22,484
Did you even mean it?

610
00:29:22,582 --> 00:29:24,890
Of course. Did you?

611
00:29:25,070 --> 00:29:28,156
Lieutenant Hunt, we're having
a problem with your patient.

612
00:29:29,280 --> 00:29:30,610
On my way.

613
00:29:40,633 --> 00:29:42,583
The chest tube started coming out
when we were transferring her.

614
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:43,825
All I have to do
is reposition it,

615
00:29:43,882 --> 00:29:45,419
but if we give her any more
morphine for the pain,

616
00:29:45,476 --> 00:29:46,480
we're gonna
have to intubate.

617
00:29:46,537 --> 00:29:49,199
Got it. I got it.
Sana, you can get through this.

618
00:29:49,257 --> 00:29:51,406
Okay? Listen to me.
I need you to breathe.

619
00:29:51,557 --> 00:29:53,867
It hurts. I can't.

620
00:29:53,943 --> 00:29:55,296
Focus on
something else, okay?

621
00:29:55,354 --> 00:29:57,743
I want you to tell me about your
neighborhood, your family, job, kids.

622
00:29:57,800 --> 00:29:59,499
- Do you have any kids?
- Aah!

623
00:29:59,557 --> 00:30:01,330
Okay, I'm gonna tell you
about my family.

624
00:30:01,388 --> 00:30:03,273
The tall, red-headed guy
yelling at everybody?

625
00:30:03,401 --> 00:30:05,749
That's my brother. He drives me
crazy most of the time.

626
00:30:05,807 --> 00:30:07,671
No, all of the time.

627
00:30:08,504 --> 00:30:11,695
That sounds like my brother.
Yeah?

628
00:30:11,795 --> 00:30:14,476
He is my heart.
He means well.

629
00:30:14,534 --> 00:30:16,031
Yeah.

630
00:30:20,184 --> 00:30:22,398
Yeah. Mine too.

631
00:30:27,551 --> 00:30:28,732
Let's get her
on the next chopper!

632
00:30:28,789 --> 00:30:30,504
I'm on it!

633
00:30:31,560 --> 00:30:34,012
- Major Hunt.
- Hi. It's me.

634
00:30:34,070 --> 00:30:36,123
I need to ride back
on the medical chopper.

635
00:30:36,181 --> 00:30:37,426
My patient's
freaking out.

636
00:30:37,520 --> 00:30:38,819
Well, you know
that's against protocol.

637
00:30:38,876 --> 00:30:40,129
And...

638
00:30:40,237 --> 00:30:41,606
Nathan cheated on me.

639
00:30:41,720 --> 00:30:43,153
He what?

640
00:30:43,348 --> 00:30:46,278
So I really don't want
to have to ride back with him,

641
00:30:46,336 --> 00:30:47,551
but if I-it's
against protocol...

642
00:30:47,608 --> 00:30:49,450
Screw protocol.
Get on the chopper.

643
00:30:49,542 --> 00:30:51,450
- Are you sure?
- It's my call, and I'm sure.

644
00:30:51,515 --> 00:30:52,708
That son of a bitch.

645
00:30:53,462 --> 00:30:55,962
Okay.
Thanks, Owen.

646
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:01,472
How you feeling?

647
00:31:01,538 --> 00:31:03,284
Like a truck hit me.

648
00:31:03,666 --> 00:31:05,544
But happy to be alive,
ma'am.

649
00:31:06,353 --> 00:31:09,106
I wonder if they'll electrocute
him here or fly him back home.

650
00:31:09,322 --> 00:31:10,973
Why are they
talking that way?

651
00:31:11,031 --> 00:31:13,629
He was the second shooter.
They're pretty upset.

652
00:31:13,687 --> 00:31:16,075
No, he wasn't. Second shooter
was an Iraqi woman.

653
00:31:16,133 --> 00:31:17,762
This guy was trying
to stop her.

654
00:31:30,145 --> 00:31:33,161
It's all good.
You're gonna be okay.

655
00:31:39,312 --> 00:31:42,448
Megan! Megan!

656
00:31:42,874 --> 00:31:44,871
Megan! Stop!

657
00:31:44,930 --> 00:31:47,677
Stop! Megan!!

658
00:31:47,994 --> 00:31:49,443
Stop it!

659
00:31:49,501 --> 00:31:52,386
♪♪

660
00:31:52,444 --> 00:31:55,562
♪♪

661
00:31:55,620 --> 00:31:57,810
Eagle 2, return... base.

662
00:32:05,010 --> 00:32:06,509
Repeat!

663
00:32:06,593 --> 00:32:09,293
Eagle 2,
return to base immediately!

664
00:32:19,439 --> 00:32:22,338
Riggs never said anything.
All this time.

665
00:32:23,342 --> 00:32:25,963
Yeah. Well...

666
00:32:26,236 --> 00:32:28,111
he's a good guy.

667
00:32:28,514 --> 00:32:30,278
Yeah.

668
00:32:32,690 --> 00:32:35,010
You remember
that family trip we took,

669
00:32:35,320 --> 00:32:36,611
somewhere in California,

670
00:32:36,669 --> 00:32:39,168
when I left the map
at the rest-stop bathroom?

671
00:32:39,241 --> 00:32:41,111
Oh, yeah. Yeah.
How could I forget?

672
00:32:41,169 --> 00:32:42,424
Dad was furious.

673
00:32:42,515 --> 00:32:45,096
And he refused to pull over
and ask for directions.

674
00:32:45,154 --> 00:32:46,166
Yep.

675
00:32:46,225 --> 00:32:49,964
And after him and Mom arguing
for hours and us complaining,

676
00:32:50,265 --> 00:32:52,538
he finally said,
"Screw it!"

677
00:32:52,651 --> 00:32:54,785
And he just,
like, pulled over.

678
00:32:54,897 --> 00:32:58,378
And we played in the water for
hours until the sun went down.

679
00:32:58,436 --> 00:32:59,833
I don't even remember
where we were going,

680
00:32:59,890 --> 00:33:02,464
but... I just...

681
00:33:02,756 --> 00:33:04,808
I've never forgotten
that beach.

682
00:33:08,514 --> 00:33:11,445
On my hardest days,
I would lose myself in that memory.

683
00:33:12,747 --> 00:33:15,930
Pretend that the desert sand
was the beach,

684
00:33:16,766 --> 00:33:20,828
that the screams and yelling were
laughter and sea gulls.

685
00:33:21,159 --> 00:33:23,953
And I could fake everything
but the water.

686
00:33:24,108 --> 00:33:27,632
And I promised myself,
if I ever get out...

687
00:33:29,781 --> 00:33:33,964
I am going to live
by the ocean, in California,

688
00:33:34,211 --> 00:33:37,320
and I'm gonna feel
that water every day.

689
00:33:43,243 --> 00:33:46,875
I always imagined us raising our
families together, you know?

690
00:33:47,953 --> 00:33:52,211
Next door, or a few blocks,
near Mom and Dad.

691
00:33:53,533 --> 00:33:55,863
Camping trips
and cookouts.

692
00:33:57,788 --> 00:33:59,680
Dad's gone, Owen.

693
00:34:00,984 --> 00:34:03,156
And you don't have
any kids.

694
00:34:04,214 --> 00:34:06,445
How exactly would
that dream work out?

695
00:34:09,042 --> 00:34:12,336
You are the most loyal person
I have ever known.

696
00:34:12,930 --> 00:34:14,889
But you're loyal
to ideas, too.

697
00:34:15,018 --> 00:34:17,351
Ideas and ideals.

698
00:34:19,448 --> 00:34:21,859
My beach plan
makes me happy.

699
00:34:21,999 --> 00:34:24,383
Like, "I can feel it
in my fingers" happy.

700
00:34:24,551 --> 00:34:27,828
I want that for you.
I want to see you happy.

701
00:34:28,539 --> 00:34:30,311
And that might mean that
you're gonna have to break up

702
00:34:30,368 --> 00:34:31,859
with some of your ideals.

703
